section.section:
"Capitalized cost" shall include to the extent capitalized and amortized as set forth in paragraph (2) of this subsection:
Taxes, registration, license, acquisition, administration, assignment, and other similar fees;
Charges for insurance, an extended warranty, mechanical repair contract, service contract, vehicle maintenance agreement, and any other similar charge;
Charges for a waiver of the contractual obligation to pay the gap amount;
Charges for accessories and installation of accessories;
Charges for delivering, servicing, repairing, or improving the vehicle; and
Charges for other goods, services, and benefits incidental to the consumer lease transaction.

"Lease" does not include:
A lease intended as security as defined in § 11-127.1(a) of the Transportation Article;
A lease which meets the definition of a credit sale in Federal Regulation Z, 12 C.F.R. § 226.2(A);
A lease for agricultural, business, or commercial purposes; or
A lease made to an organization.
